4 A BILL FOR AN ACT ENTITLED: “AN ACT PROHIBITING THE PLACEMENT OF SENTENCED
5 DEFENDANTS IN THE STATE FORENSIC MENTAL HEALTH FACILITY AT GALEN; AMENDING SECTION
6 46-14-312, MCA; AND PROVIDING AN IMMEDIATE EFFECTIVE DATE.”
7
8 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF MONTANA:
9
10 Section 1. Section 46-14-312, MCA, is amended to read:
11 "46-14-312. Sentence to be imposed. (1) If the court finds that the defendant at the time of the
12 commission of the offense of which the defendant was convicted did not suffer from a mental disease or
13 disorder as described in 46-14-311, the court shall sentence the defendant as provided in Title 46, chapter 18.
14 (2) (a) If the court finds that the defendant at the time of the commission of the offense suffered
15 from a mental disease or disorder or developmental disability as described in 46-14-311, any mandatory
16 minimum sentence prescribed by law for the offense need not apply. The court shall sentence the defendant to
17 be committed to the custody of the director of the department of public health and human services to be placed,
18 after consideration of the recommendations of the professionals providing treatment to the defendant and
19 recommendations of the professionals who have evaluated the defendant, in an appropriate correctional facility,
20 in a mental health facility, as defined in 53-21-102, but not the state forensic mental health facility at Galen, in a
21 residential facility, as defined in 53-20-102, or in a developmental disabilities facility, as defined in 53-20-202,
22 for custody, care, and treatment for a definite period of time not to exceed the maximum term of imprisonment
23 that could be imposed under subsection (1).
24 (b) The director may, after considering the recommendations of the professionals providing
25 treatment to the defendant and recommendations of the professionals who have evaluated the defendant,
26 subsequently transfer the defendant to another correctional, mental health, residential, or developmental
27 disabilities facility that will better serve the defendant's custody, care, and treatment needs.
28 (c) The authority of the court with regard to sentencing is the same as authorized in Title 46,
